<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100637331940052></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100637331940052><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4197&mid=100637331940052>Gauntlets of the black</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4197&mid=100637331940052#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=64677><span id=Sage>xaanru</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>727 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 21st 3:08 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If the pricing on these is even near accurate, I would get gauntlets of the black instead. They have ac15, 4str, and 3 wis. I know the wis isn't super helpful on a warrior, unless you're tradeskilling and wis is higher. However, in my opinion, The 4 raw ac is worth losing 20hp and 1 strength. My level 17 human (weak) warrior was recently buffed with storm strength by a nice passerby, and currently has 180 strength with the buff, and thats just with Iksar scaled gloves, which are definitely not as good as these or gaunts of the black. I did hit for a bit more damage, but it didn't seem to make that much difference on my taunt, since I can hold taunt even over some lvl 18 and 19 warriors by dual wielding icetooth's claws and a blackened alloy longsword. However, 4 raw ac seems to translate to about 6 actual ac, which makes a large difference in the damage I take in a battle. since the point is for me to TAKE damage, not dish it, I'd take the Gaunts of the black any day. The ac difference will decrease damage by more than 20hp in any melee, and 1 strength is nearly meaningless. I can cook up some beer baised bear and make up for that, and then some.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
